descript.abstract: This map layer consists of federally owned or administered lands of the United States, Puerto Rico, and the U.S. Virgin Islands. For the most part, only areas of 320 acres or more are included; some smaller areas deemed to be important or significant are also included. There may be private inholdings within the boundaries of Federal lands in this map layer. Some established Federal lands which are larger than 320 acres are not included in this map layer, because their boundaries were not available from the owning or administering agency.
descript.purpose: These data are intended for geographic display and analysis at the national level, and for large regional areas. The data should be displayed and analyzed at scales appropriate for 1:1,000,000-scale data. No responsibility is assumed by the National Atlas of the United States in the use of these data.

dataqual.logic: The map layer was checked for topological consistency using ArcGIS. No other checks for logical consistency were performed on this map layer.
dataqual.complete: This map layer includes Federal land features for all fifty United States, the District of Columbia, Puerto Rico, and the U.S. Virgin Islands. The minimum map resolution is 320 acres. Generally, features under this size are not shown. There may be private inholdings within the boundaries of Federal lands in this map layer. Some established Federal lands which are larger than the minimum map resolution are not included in this map layer because their boundaries were not available from the owning or administering agency.

procstep.procdesc: All the data sources were downloaded and combined into a single geodatabase. Boundary lines were generalized as needed for the data scale; areas not meeting the minimum mapping unit were deleted, attribute values were checked and adjusted as necessary, and the map layer was saved in shapefile and in file geodatabase formats.

attr.attrdef: The URL, or Uniform Resource Locator, is the address of a page on the World Wide Web. The address, which provides the basis for establishing an electronic link from a client to the physical location of the page on an Internet server, consists of a server name, file path, and the page's file name. A URL in this map layer is usually the address of a Federal agency website. For example, http://www.nps.gov/findapark/index.htm is the address of a National Park Service page that allows you to locate a park in the National Park system.
attr.attrdefs: National Atlas of the United States
